<h1>Task manager APP API Documentation</h1>

<h2>POST /users</h2>
<p>Creates a new user and generates an authentication token.</p>
<h3>Request Body</h3>
<p>The request body should contain the following fields:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>name</code>: A string representing the user's name.</li>
  <li><code>email</code>: A string representing the user's email address.</li>
  <li><code>password</code>: A string representing the user's password.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Response</h3>
<p>The response will contain the following fields:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>user</code>: An object representing the new user.</li>
  <li><code>token</code>: A string representing the authentication token.</li>
</ul>

<h2>POST /users/login</h2>
<p>Logs in a user and generates an authentication token.</p>
<h3>Request Body</h3>
<p>The request body should contain the following fields:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>email</code>: A string representing the user's email address.</li>
  <li><code>password</code>: A string representing the user's password.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Response</h3>
<p>The response will contain the following fields:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>user</code>: An object representing the logged in user.</li>
  <li><code>token</code>: A string representing the authentication token.</li>
</ul>

<h2>POST /users/logout</h2>
<p>Logs out the currently authenticated user.</p>
<h3>Headers</h3>
<p>The request should include an <code>Authorization</code> header with the authentication token.</p>

<h2>POST /users/logoutAll</h2>
<p>Logs out all sessions for the currently authenticated user.</p>
<h3>Headers</h3>
<p>The request should include an <code>Authorization</code> header with the authentication token.</p>

<h2>GET /users</h2>
<p>Gets a list of all users.</p>
<h3>Headers</h3>
<p>The request should include an <code>Authorization</code> header with the authentication token.</p>
<h3>Response</h3>
<p>The response will contain an array of user objects.</p>

<h2>GET /users/me</h2>
<p>Gets the currently authenticated user.</p>
<h3>Headers</h3>
<p>The request should include an <code>Authorization</code> header with the authentication token.</p>
<h3>Response</h3>
<p>The response will contain an object representing the authenticated user.</p>

<h2>GET /users/:id</h2>
<p>Gets a user with the specified ID.</p>
<h3>Path Parameters</h3>
<p>The request should include the user's ID as a path parameter.</p>
<h3>Response</h3>
<p>The response will contain an object representing the requested user.</p>

<h2>PATCH /users/me</h2>
<p>Updates the currently authenticated user.</p>
<h3>Request Body</h3>
<p>The request body should contain one or more of the following fields:</p>
<ul>
  <li><code>name</code>: A string representing the user's name.</li>
  <li><code>email</code>: A string representing the user's email address.</li>
  <li><code>password</code>: A string representing the user's password.</li>
  <li><code>age</code>: A number representing the user's age.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Headers</h3>
<p>The request should include an <code>Authorization</code> header with the authentication token.</p>
<h3>Response</h3>
<p>The response will contain an object representing the updated user.</p>

<h2>DELETE /users/me</h2>
<p>Deletes the currently authenticated user and allassociated tasks.</p>
<h3>Headers</h3>
<p>The request should include an <code>Authorization</code> header with the authentication token.</p>
<h3>Response</h3>
<p>The response will contain an object representing the deleted user.</p>